================================================================================
Data license
================================================================================

The released gene-disease evidence data in this repository — the contents of
`releases/` and the referenced source-snapshot payloads under
`data/source_snapshots/` — is made available under the Creative Commons
Attribution 4.0 International License (CC BY 4.0), to the extent that the
curation, normalization, and compilation are protectable. Underlying source
records remain subject to their upstream terms listed under "Sources" below.

  Full legal text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode
  Summary:         https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

You are free to share and adapt the data for any purpose, including
commercially, provided you give appropriate credit, indicate if changes were
made, and do not imply endorsement by the author or by any upstream source.

================================================================================
Attribution
================================================================================

When redistributing or building on this data, cite the dataset and preserve the
upstream source attribution. Suggested dataset citation:

  Serkan Altuntas. "Gene-Disease Evidence Data" (release <version>).
  https://serkan.ai/gene-disease-evidence/ — licensed under CC BY 4.0.

See CITATION.cff for machine-readable citation metadata.

================================================================================
Sources (upstream terms preserved)
================================================================================

This dataset is derived from third-party sources, each under its own terms:

  - HGNC (HUGO Gene Nomenclature Committee) — Creative Commons Zero (CC0 1.0).
  - MONDO Disease Ontology — Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 (CC BY 4.0).
    Used for disease identity/context. CC BY 4.0 attribution to MONDO is
    required; this is the binding constraint on the combined dataset's license.
  - Open Targets Platform — Creative Commons Zero (CC0 1.0).
  - ClinVar / NCBI — U.S. National Library of Medicine public data; reuse is
    subject to NCBI policies (attribution requested, no endorsement implied).

Source names denote provenance only and do not imply endorsement by those
sources. Open Targets scores are source-attributed signals, not truth or
clinical validity. ClinVar rows are variant/condition context only.

================================================================================
Research-use scope & disclaimers
================================================================================

This is a research-use, source-attributed gene-disease *hypothesis* index. It is
NOT medical advice, diagnosis, treatment guidance, patient risk prediction,
clinical decision support, a claim of clinical certainty, or a manuscript-grade
biomedical dataset. Verify against primary sources before any downstream use.

Releases with a `-dev` suffix are development artifacts and must not be cited as
scientific evidence. Public-candidate releases (v0.1.x, v0.2.0) are review-gated
drafts published for transparency.

================================================================================
Code
================================================================================

This repository contains data, schemas, documentation, and citation metadata
only. It does not contain the production pipeline; no license is granted to any
pipeline implementation not present here.
